ru\u0144 2005, pp.&nbsp;279,315 || for Galicia \"primary balance\" relied on \"fragmentary and often incomplete documentation\" and witnesses' testimonies\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#d0e7ff;\"| [[Paul Robert Magocsi|P.R. Magocsi]] || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || 50k || ||Magocsi; A History of Ukraine, p 681 || \"among the more reasonable estimates\" \n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#d0e7ff;\"|[[Niall Ferguson]]|| \u2013 || \u2013 || 60-80k || -|| ||''The war of the world'', 2007{{citation needed|date=January 2013}}  || Fergusson is citing other authors (which ones?)\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#d0e7ff;\"| John Paul Himka || \u2013 || \u2013 || 100k || - || || [https://archive.is/20120720113547/http://ualberta.academia.edu/JohnPaulHimka/Papers/493886/Interventions_Challenging_the_Myths_of_Twentieth-Century_Ukrainian_History ''Interventions: Challenging the Myths of Twentieth-Century Ukrainian history''], 2001 || [http://www.h-net.org/reviews/showrev.php?id=14704]\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#d0e7ff;\"| [[Per Anders Rudling]] || 40-70k || \u2013 ||-||||7k|| ''[https://www.academia.edu/380654/_Theory_and_Practice_Historical_Representation_of_the_War_Time_Activities_of_the_OUN-UPA_the_Organization_of_Ukrainian_Nationalists_-_the_Ukrainian_Insurgent_Army_East_European_Jewish_Affairs_36_2_December_2006_163-189 Theory and Practice]'', 2006 || below note\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#d0e7ff;\"| Rossolinski-Liebe ||  ||-|| \u2013 ||70-100k||-|| ''The Ukrainian national revolution'' (2011),  ''Celebrating Fascism...'' (2010) || [https://web.archive.org/web/20120312175935/http://zomobo.net/Timothy-Snyder] (?)\n|-\n| Ewa Siemaszko || 60k || 70k || 130k || 133k || ||''Bilans zbrodni'', 2010 [https://web.archive.org/web/20110728070508/http://ipn.gov.pl/download.php?s=1&id=25096] || According to Rudling it is the most extensive study of the Polish casualties (Rudling, \"The OUN, the UPA and the Holocaust...\", p.&nbsp;50)\n|-\n| Marek Jasiak || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2013 || 60-70k || ||Redrawing Nations, p174 || \"In Podole, Volhynia, and Lublin\"\n|-\n| Terles ||  ||50k  ||  60-70k  || \u2013 || 100-200k || ||In ''Ethnic Cleansing'' p.&nbsp;61\n|- \n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#f9b;\"| Karta || 35k || 29.8k || \u2013 || \u2013 ||6.5k || \"Polska-Ukraina\", t.7, 2000, p.&nbsp;159, cited by Kalishchuk: here [https://web.archive.org/web/20150414180038/http://www.nbuv.gov.ua/portal/soc_gum/Ukrpol/2010-2011_3-4/PDF/20Kalishchuk.pdf] || Karta based mostly on: Siemaszko for Volhynia (documented number) and Cz.Blicharski for Tarnopol voivodsh.\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#ffffc0;\"|[http://www.birmingham.ac.uk/schools/government-society/departments/political-science-international-studies/staff/profiles/wolczuk-kataryna.aspx Katarina Wolczuk] || \u2013 || -|| \u2013 || 60-100k || ||\"The Difficulties of Polish\u2013Ukrainian Historical Reconciliation,\" paper published by the Royal Institute of International Affairs, London, 2002, cited by Marples|| \n|- \n|  style=\"text-align:left; background:#d0e7ff;\"| Alexander Gogun || 25k+ || \u2013 || \u2013 ||||||Lib.OUN-UPA.org.ua<ref name=\"lib.oun\">{{cite web |url=http://lib.oun-upa.org.ua/gogun/dis_r02.html |title=\u0414\u0435\u044f\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c \u0432\u043e\u043e\u0440\u0443\u0436\u0451\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043d\u0430\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u0440\u0440\u0438\u0442\u043e-\u0440\u0438\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u043f\u0430\u0434\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0435\u0439 \u0423\u0421\u0421\u0420 (1943\u20131949) |year=2005 |author=Alexander Gogun |publisher=Lib.OUN-UPA.org.ua |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130321064413/http://lib.oun-upa.org.ua